.TH "mesh_path_error_tx" 9 "mesh_path_error_tx" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mesh_path_error_tx \- Sends a PERR mesh management frame
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mesh_path_error_tx
.BI "(struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata "  ","
.BI "u8 ttl "  ","
.BI "const u8 *target "  ","
.BI "u32 target_sn "  ","
.BI "u16 target_rcode "  ","
.BI "const u8 *ra "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdata" 12
local mesh subif
.IP "ttl" 12
allowed remaining hops
.IP "target" 12
broken destination
.IP "target_sn" 12
SN of the broken destination
.IP "target_rcode" 12
reason code for this PERR
.IP "ra" 12
node this frame is addressed to
.SH "NOTE"
This function may be called with driver locks taken that the driver
also acquires in the TX path.  To avoid a deadlock we don't transmit the
frame directly but add it to the pending queue instead.
